# COMMA Mobile — Migration Mega Plan (.agent)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# This is the authoritative step-by-step migration guide from the COMMA web PWA
# (vanilla JS + Dexie + CSS) to the Expo/React Native mobile app.
#
# PURPOSE: Keep every future AI conversation on-track by providing a checklist
# of exactly what needs to be built, in what order, and why.
#
# STATUS KEY:  ✅ Done  |  🔲 Not Started  |  🔨 In Progress
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## 0. CURRENT STATE SNAPSHOT (Baseline)

### Web App (SOURCE — what we're migrating FROM)
- Stack: Vanilla JS, esbuild, Dexie (IndexedDB), CSS custom properties
- Router: Hash-based (#/dashboard, #/shifts, etc.)
- 18 views: dashboard, shifts, analytics, expenses, tax, vehicles, schedule,
  goals, reports, import, settings, support, onboarding, notifications,
  about, print, import-help, debug
- Design System: DM Sans/Serif/Mono fonts, CSS tokens (colors, spacing, radii,
  shadows, transitions), light/dark/auto theming
- Complex features: shift timer with big-clock overlay, GPS tracking, 
  platform registry (DoorDash/UberEats/Foodora/Skip/Instacart/AmazonFlex),
  widget-based bento dashboard, sparkline KPI cards, analytics charts,
  expense categories, goal types, badges/XP, notifications, backup/drive,
  CSV import, PDF reports, search overlay, PWA install
- Data: 14 Dexie object stores (users, platforms, shifts, expenses, vehicles,
  vehicleMaintenanceLogs, vehicleOdometerLog, fuelPrices, goals, goalHistory,
  badges, xpLog, challenges, notifications, backupLog, appState)

### Mobile App (TARGET — current state)
- Stack: Expo SDK 56, React Native 0.85, TypeScript, Expo Router, 
  NativeWind v4 + Tailwind v3, Drizzle ORM + expo-sqlite, Zustand, 
  TanStack React Query
- Screens: 1 (index.tsx — basic dashboard with shift timer + projection card)
- Components: OnboardingWizard, OnboardingSteps, CongratulationsSheet
- UI Primitives: Button, Card, Text (shadcn-mobile / React Native Reusables)
- Schema: 4 tables (vehicles, shifts, expenses, settings)
- Stores: useActiveShift, useSettingsStore, useCounterStore (unused)

### GAP ANALYSIS
The mobile app has ~5% of the web app's feature surface. The critical path is:
1. Design system parity (colors, tokens, theming)
2. Navigation/routing scaffold (tab + stack navigation)
3. Database schema expansion (match web's 14 stores)
4. Core views (dashboard → shifts → analytics → expenses)
5. Feature modules (goals, reports, settings, etc.)
6. Polish features (badges, search, backup, notifications)

