### Step 1.1 — Design Tokens & Theme System                          ✅
Migrate the web's CSS token system to NativeWind/Tailwind equivalents.

SOURCE FILES:
  - src/css/tokens.css (color primitives, spacing, typography, radii, shadows)
  - src/css/themes.css (light/dark/auto overrides)

ACTIONS:
  □ Update tailwind.config.js to define ALL web color tokens:
    - Brand: #10b981 (--color-brand)
    - Platform colors: doordash=#ff3008, ubereats=#142328, foodora=#e2006a,
      skip=#f96302, instacart=#43b02a, amazonflex=#ff9900, other=#6b7280
    - Semantic light: bg=#fafaf8, surface=#ffffff, surface-raised=#f2f0eb,
      border=#e5e2da, text-primary=#1a1916, text-secondary=#6b6860,
      text-muted=#a09d96, success=#22c55e, warning=#f59e0b, danger=#ef4444,
      info=#3b82f6
    - Semantic dark: bg=#12110f, surface=#1c1b18, surface-raised=#262522,
      border=#3d3a35, text-primary=#f4f2ed, text-secondary=#b8b4ab,
      text-muted=#7a7670
  □ Update src/global.css HSL variables to match web tokens exactly
  □ Add spacing scale: 4,8,12,16,20,24,32,40,48,64
  □ Add radii: sm=6, md=10, lg=16, xl=24, pill=999
  □ Add shadow definitions matching web's shadow-sm/md/lg/xl
  □ Configure font family references (DM Sans equivalent or Inter)
  □ Set up dark mode as default class="dark" on root

VALIDATION:
  - Create a ThemeShowcase component rendering all tokens
  - Compare side-by-side with web app in dark mode

