## PHASE 2: DATA LAYER — Schema Expansion & Store Architecture
## Target: Full data model parity with the web app
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Step 2.1 — Drizzle Schema Expansion                               🔲
Expand the 4-table schema to match web's full data model.

SOURCE FILES:
  - src/core/db.js (STORES_V3 definition, DEFAULT_USER, APP_STATE_KEY_DEFAULTS)

ACTIONS:
  □ Add new tables to src/database/schema.ts:
    - platforms (id, name, color, terminology JSON, weeklyGoal, monthlyGoal,
      taxRatePct, notes, priority, active, addedAt, deactivatedAt, 
      platformSpecific JSON)
    - goals (id, type, scope, platformId, target, active, createdAt)
    - goalHistory (id, goalId, periodStart, value)
    - badges (id, name, description, icon, unlockedAt, notified)
    - xpLog (id, amount, reason, createdAt)
    - challenges (id, active, type, config JSON)
    - notifications (id, type, title, body, read, dismissed, createdAt, data JSON)
    - appState (key, value, updatedAt)
    - vehicleMaintenanceLogs (id, vehicleId, date, type, cost, notes)
    - vehicleOdometerLog (id, vehicleId, date, reading)
    - fuelPrices (id, vehicleId, date, pricePerUnit, totalCost, liters)
    - backupLog (id, createdAt, type, status)
  □ Expand existing tables to match web's fields:
    - shifts: add date (YYYY-MM-DD string), platformId, provinceId, 
      grossEarnings (cents), bonusEarnings (cents), tips (cents), 
      deliveryCount, durationMinutes, deadMilesKm, customFields JSON,
      deletedAt (soft delete), onlineStartTime, onlineEndTime
    - expenses: add platformId, provinceId, hstPaid, confirmedPaid, 
      isRecurring, recurringInterval, deletedAt, description
    - vehicles: add make, model, year, odometerStart, fuelType, 
      insuranceCost, notes
  □ Expand users/settings to store full DEFAULT_USER shape from web:
    - Store as JSON in settings table (key="user") OR create a users table
  □ Generate new Drizzle migration via `npm run db:generate`
  □ Write migration logic to preserve existing data

VALIDATION:
  - Run `npx expo start`, confirm DB initializes without errors
  - Insert and query from each new table via Drizzle Studio

