## EXECUTION RULES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. ALWAYS complete a step fully before starting the next
2. ALWAYS update the status checkbox (🔲→🔨→✅) when starting/finishing a step  
3. NEVER skip Phase 1 — it's the visual foundation everything else depends on
4. ALWAYS refer to web source files listed under each step for exact behavior
5. ALWAYS test on Android device/emulator after each step (not just web)
6. ALWAYS use expo-sqlite via Drizzle — no web-only localStorage hacks
7. ALWAYS keep the Platform.OS === "web" guard in _layout.tsx for SQLiteProvider
8. ALWAYS read Expo SDK 56 docs at https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v56.0.0/
9. When building UI, compare with web app running at localhost:3000
10. Prefer bottom sheets over full modals for forms (mobile UX best practice)

## DEPENDENCY NOTES
- react-native-svg: needed for sparklines/charts (install + rebuild native)
- expo-location: needed for GPS tracking (Phase 5.6)
- expo-notifications: needed for push notifications (Phase 4.7)
- expo-print / expo-sharing: needed for PDF export (Phase 4.3)
- react-native-chart-kit or victory-native: needed for analytics charts
- fuse.js: needed for fuzzy search (Phase 5.3)
- @react-native-async-storage/async-storage: needed for timer persistence

## FILE NAMING CONVENTIONS
- Screens: app/(tabs)/screenName.tsx or app/feature/index.tsx
- Components: src/components/feature/ComponentName.tsx
- Stores: store/useFeatureStore.ts
- Hooks: hooks/useFeatureName.ts
- Utils: utils/featureName.ts
- Registry: src/registry/registryName.ts
